124
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:36,780
talking about there.

125
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:40,860
I need to go find actual research to back up what I'm saying there.

126
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:45,280
So that revision is a lot of really big changes.

127
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,830
So I've done some planning.

128
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:47,590
I run it.

129
00:05:47,590 --> 00:05:48,460
I reflect on it.

130
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:49,350
I revise it.

131
00:05:49,350 --> 00:05:51,330
And then I run it again.

132
00:05:51,330 --> 00:05:55,590
But now I'm in phase two, the second pass on the speech.

133
00:05:55,590 --> 00:06:00,770
I would say if I'm going to label this one, this is redefining the speech.

134
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:01,950
So I'm running it.

135
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:06,290
Certainly, I'm better on time, but I know the main parts of the

136
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:08,050
presentation a little bit better.

137
00:06:08,050 --> 00:06:10,120
Yeah, I'm almost pretty close to reading it.

138
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,300
I'm relying pretty heavily on that outline.

139
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,980
But I can remember some basic things.

140
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:16,890
I remember where the huge chunks of the presentation are.

141
00:06:16,890 --> 00:06:19,060
So I run it that second time.

142
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:20,660
Then I sit down and reflect on it.

143
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:22,950
And now I've got some narrower reflections.

144
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:25,570
There's some parts I'm like, that was fun and awesome.

145
00:06:25,570 --> 00:06:28,310
And then there are other parts where I'm like, I'm bored myself.

146
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:30,480
That was terrible.

147
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:33,860
So I want to reflect on what are some of the big chunks of the presentation?

148
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:34,580
Which ones are working?

149
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:35,710
And which ones aren't?

150
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,570
And again, I'm going through revision.

151
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:42,160
Maybe now I'm cutting entire points or entire sections of the speech.

152
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:45,300
I may or may not be doing massive goal changes.

153
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,460
because I've already gone through that pass.

154
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:50,650
But I'm really starting to take a harder look at inclusion, exclusion.

155
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:52,020
What gets into the speech?

156
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:53,810
What do I just not have time for?

157
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:56,510
What needs to be kicked out of the speech?

158
00:06:56,510 --> 00:06:57,400
So I've run it.

159
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,110
I've reflected.

160
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,240
I've revised it.

161
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,130
And then we go into round three.

162
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:02,190
So I take another pass.

163
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:05,350
If I'm labeling this one, this is getting all those main

164
00:07:05,350 --> 00:07:06,610
